About the Author
Tarkan Batgun: Building Football’s Decision Architecture

For Tarkan Batgun, scouting was never only about identifying talent. It was always about building systems that reduce error, protect clubs from emotional decision-making, and create a sustainable competitive advantage.

Across decades of work inside clubs, federations, education and technology, one reality remained constant: football continued to make expensive decisions with incomplete structures. That is where The Book of Scouting Volume One begins. It was written to bridge the gap between traditional football intuition and modern decision architecture, bringing together practical experience, executive leadership, and the technological future of recruitment into one unified framework.

Because great recruitment is never only about finding players. It is about building the structure that makes the right decisions possible.
 
A Pioneer in the Field

Tarkan Batgun is a dual Australian-Turkish citizen and a globally recognized pioneer in football recruitment technology and scouting education. As the Founder and CEO of Comparisonator, an AI-powered football data analytics platform used by elite clubs, agencies and international media worldwide, Tarkan has spent over two decades at the intersection of econometrics, technology, and professional football.

In the industry, he is widely regarded as the expert who introduced and institutionalized the modern concept of scouting across various countries. During his tenure as Director of Scouting at Bursaspor in Turkish Super League, he designed and implemented the “Scouting Laboratory” alongside legendary Head Coach Christophe Daum. This revolutionary project earned the Innovation Award at the 2014 Sportstec Innovation Conference in London. His work successfully combined live observation with advanced performance analysis, helping redefine how recruitment departments operate.
 
Bridging Education and Industry

Tarkan’s influence extends into both the boardroom and the classroom. He served as a Board Member at Altınordu FK and spent over a decade as a Lecturer at Haliç University Physical Education & Sports Faculty, teaching Performance Analysis to the next generation of football professionals.

Since 2010, he has been an architect of Match Analysis and Scouting courses at various federations, helping shape the methodology used by national-level coaches, scouts and football decision-makers.
 
A Global Consultant

For more than 15 years, Tarkan has served as a management consultant for leading sports technology companies including Wyscout, SoccerLab, and Sportstec Australia (Hudl). Between 2014 and 2021, he led the NIKE Türkiye Scouting Team, identifying future elite-level talents.
 
Academic and Media Presence

A graduate of Istanbul University (Econometrics) and Marmara University (Computer Programming), with MBA studies at the University of Wollongong, Tarkan combines a data scientist’s mind with a scout’s eye.

He is a frequent keynote speaker and moderator at global football summits, including SFS Italy, Football Forum Hungary, and the Azerbaijan Football Conference. As a respected media analyst on Sports TV and A Spor, he is known for bringing structure, evidence, and objective thinking into public football discourse.


